Text.string: Ah, Athenas, huh? Yeah, been meaning to visit but, uh... haven't had the chance, what with... running a giant corporation and everything. Just haven't found the time.
Well, you may not have brought an army of thousands, Vault Hunter, but, uh... I hope you can kill like one!
So, how's my good buddy Zer0 doing? Atlas would be rubble without him. He is pretty cool.
Just as Atlas was gettin' back to form, Maliwan shows up and invades. I mean, what the hell, man? Why me?
I don't care what Katagawa says, this merger will happen over my cold dead body.||—Which is probably the point.
All I ever wanted was a corporation I could call my own. This is my shot, Vault Hunter. You can't throw away your shot!
Yes! That creepy business stalker is DEAD!
Thanks for saving my ass, Vault Hunter. You really came through for me.
Man, does Zer0 know how to make an entrance, or what?
I'm a man of my word. That Vault is all yours. No crossy-backsies, promise!
Rest in peace, Rhys-ball. Rest in peace.
The tide is turning! All right!
You stopped the Calypsos, huh? That's, well, it's—it's -- it's just great, ya know? Just great.
Now that you saved the world and everything, maybe me, you and Vaughn could, ya know, hang? Heh-heh... just sayin'!
So, the Firehawk's gone, huh? Is she, like, uh... dead gone or “cool mystery where'd she go” gone? It's a thing I've been wondering.
Say, what're your thoughts on appearing in an Atlas ad campaign? For free! It'd be fun, right? Oh, oh, oh—just say, um... “I couldn't have saved the galaxy without ATLAS!” Go on, try it out.
Just, uh, walkin' right up to a CEO, huh? You're a disruptor, I like that.
Ever considered the exciting field of cleaning up my messes?
Oh, me and my buddy Vaughn had all sorts of crazy adventures. I should, uh, TALES you about it sometime, uh... but I'm very busy at the moment.
Have I ever been in love? Heh-heh, thanks for asking! Sorta personal though, ya know? But because you asked... I'm kinda sad now.
I used to work for Hyperion Corporation but, uh... well, that story's got a long TALE...
I am not a Vault Hunter. Well, true, I hunted *a* Vault but, uh... Okay, fine, I'm a LAPSED Vault Hunter. Y'happy now?
Climbing the corporate ladder is exhausting. Y'know, sometimes I just wanna climb a REAL ladder, you know?
Hey! It's you! Blankin' on the, uh, the, uh, the, uh... the name... but I know that winning... gun.
People in the corporate world are all “go go go!” Not you, though. It's, um... oddly unsettling.
I thought hangin' out with Zer0 might help my poetry skills, but I still have to count haiku syllables on my fingers.
If you see main man Vaughn back on Pandora, tell him main man Rhys said, uh... tell him Rhys said, “yo.”
Y'know, last time a Vault opened on Promethea, Atlas rose like a phoenix. And then, uh, died, like a phoenix does. Kinda torn both ways on this one.
It's Vault-o-clock, baby! Heh-heh... Is, is that catching on yet?
I grew a mustache to inspire my troops. That's leadership! Right? Right.
I'm sorry about your friend. I know she was a good friend to a lot of your people.
I guess Zer0's goin' with you guys now, but, uh... Just—bring him back in one piece, okay? We need him around here.
Ah, you're back! Where'd you run off to? You smell like... swamp. And sadness, and... uh, more swamp.
Are we growing apart? No, just kidding. We're good, right? Right? Right.
Got some intel that you're running a resistance with Jakobs Corporation? Hey, what are they resisting? Modern manufacturing materials? Boom!
Heard through the grapevine that you went to Eden-6. Man, I heard that place was paradise!
Hey there... you! Heh-heh... Meridian is on the road to mending! Yeah, it's—it's a long and... land-mined road.
My people have been hammering me about the Vault you opened. If you found some, uh... juicy Eridian tech in there, you'd tell your old pal Rhys, right?
Hey, how's Zer0? Did he get any of my care packages yet?

Uh, so I, uh, saw that the Calypso Twins kidnapped your scientist? Haha, I feel ya! Katagawa kidnapped a bunch of mine, too. Yup, my entire aquatic combat research division is gone, so, uh... don't plan on fighting underwater for awhile.
Heya, champ! Read in CEO Quarterly that Wainwright Jakobs took back the family corp. You-uh, you-uh, you, uh, have anything to do with that?
Remember the Zanara? I heard that Katagawa had another pleasure yacht parked at some casino.
Vault Hunter! Come to check on your old pal, Rhys, eh? Nice!||—So... yeah, we have nothing to talk about. I'm a busy man. Got a corporation to run, all that.
I just—I just can't stop thinking about... Rhys-ball, ya know? That, that -- that ball, it meant... more to me than you can ever know.
Did you kick that crap outta those murderstreamers yet? If not, why the hell are you talkin' to me?
Yo, Vault Hunter! Heard you iced Troy Calypso... nice! Hhhhhated that guy.
Heya, bud. Got some intel that the legendary planet of Nekrotafeyo is real? You, uh, you wouldn't keep just a monumental discovery from your old pal Rhys, would ya?
So, added MORE Sirens to the Crimson Raiders, huh? That's... sorta selfish, don't ya think? I mean, there's a war outside my window.
Wait wait wait wait wait, Maliwan is on Nekrotafeyo? ARE YOU EFFING KIDDING ME?!
So, how's your best buds Maliwan doing? Heh-heh, just kidding... kill them all.
You came all this way to see me? So, what ancient Eridian technology that will propel Atlas to the top did you bring your best bud Rhys, huh?
So, it's lookin' pretty dire for Pandora, huh? Whatcha gonna do about that, champ?
Bee-tee-dubs. The way you took down that Zanara? I'll never forget that. Heh... R.I.P., Rhys-ball.
Vault Hunter, you fight like an animal! Only with—with, uh, opposable thumbs. So, like, a SUPER animal!
I know opening that Vault here didn't go the way you planned, but I am glad no one's coming for it anymore.
You found another Vault, didn't you? No, no—no need to admit it. I can SMELL it on you. Hussy.
Saw you on the murderstream. Lookin' good, Vault Hunter!||—What? There was nothing else on!
So, how was Nekrotafeyo, huh? Well, maybe next time you go you'll, uh, invite your best bud Rhys?
There you are, hero!
Hmmm. Wonder what Vaughn's up to... wonder if he got any of those Atlas shirts I sent him.
I haven't practiced my finger guns in a while. I bet my aim's terrible.
Down time. Cool, cool. Just... hangin' out.
[humming] Digby Vermouth... Classic!
Think I'm gonna give myself a raise. I can do that, y'know. No board approval or anything, just... BOOM. Money in the BANK.
Hey. Got a job I'm lookin' to outsource.
Hey there, you seem underemployed. Wanna join the gig economy?
Got some work for ya. Swing on by, my door's open. Or destroyed.
Hey, there's my favorite corporate ally!
Workin' hard or hardly workin'? Eh? Hahahahah! Just came up with that! Wow.
Looks like somebody's got a case of the whatever-day-it-is. Is's.
Quittin' time yet? Heh, just kiddin', it never is. What's up?
Uh-oh, here comes trouble!
Hey hey, usin' an Atlas I see. You've got good taste!
Only the best in Atlas weaponry for you, eh, Vault Hunter?
You're using a... Maliwan. Bad form. Eh, great function, though.
Walkin' up just waving Maliwan tech around, huh? I see how it is.
Help me out here.
Hey, you wanna do a thing for me?
Vault Hunter—I got a thing for ya.
Hey, it's... you! Ready to answer the call for adventure?
You look bored. Wanna... do stuff with me? Ah! That didn't come out right. And I attended that training, too...
You, uh, figured out that stuff yet?
How's it goin'? With the, uh, with the thing we talked about?
You done yet? Did I give you a deadline?
Vault Hunter! I need that thing done EOD... that means, uh... wait, what the hell does that mean? I'll get back to ya.
Hey buddy, you get sidetracked or dead, or... deadtracked? What's up?
Clockin' out.
Oh, you're leaving. I gotcha. I was done too. With our—with our whole conversation.
TGIF! That stands for “Torgue Guns are Inferior Firearms”. Been tryin' to get that thing going.
Well, bye!
You out? Cool! I'll be, uh... here!
Buy Atlas!
If you need me, contact my assistant. I'll figure out who that is... probably by tomorrow.
And I will catch you... on the flip. The flippy dip.
You're leaving! Ha! At-las-tuh. Ehhh? The guys in the humor department worked that up for me.
Meeting adjourned!
